* Task 4 fixture: resolver skeleton for dynamic edges and inline PERFORM (FR-11, FR-12, M-4)
* Demonstrates:
* - CALLNAT #VAR (dynamic) → should resolve as Unresolved(ReasonDynamic) with caller context preserved
* - PERFORM LOCAL-SUB (inline match) → should resolve to in-file definition at the Target range
*
* The dynamic call and inline PERFORM coexist to prove the resolver preserves
* both outcomes correctly and does not attempt static binding on dynamic edges.

DEFINE DATA
LOCAL
  1 PROGNAME (A30)
END DEFINE

* Dynamic call — variable target, no static binding possible
CALLNAT #PROGNAME

* Inline PERFORM — definition exists in the same file
PERFORM LOCAL-SUB

* Inline subroutine definition (same file)
DEFINE SUBROUTINE LOCAL-SUB
  MOVE 'DONE' TO PROGNAME
END SUBROUTINE

END
